Athletics Integrity Unit (AIU) had earlier flagged down the 2014 World Under-20 800m champion over whereabouts failuresBut AIU has since found Kipketer guilty and banned him for two years starting November 26, 2019 - which is the date of fourth whereabouts failure - to November 25, 2021 Kenyan middle-distance athlete Alfred Kipketer has been banned for two years for a doping offence.
Athletics Integrity Unit (AIU) had earlier flagged down the 2014 World Under-20 800m champion over whereabouts failures.
But AIU has since found Kipketer guilty and banned him for two years starting November 26, 2019 - which is the date of fourth whereabouts failure - to November 25, 2021.



